3ï¸âƒ£ What NOT to do (important)

Do not plot:

Expected carry vs realized levels

Scatter with raw values (heteroskedastic, misleading)

Portfolio PnL

Cumulative curves

Those all bake in scale choices you explicitly want to avoid.

4ï¸âƒ£ Optional but powerful: Calibration plot

This is your second diagnostic.

Plot

X-axis: Expected carry (rank-normalized)

Y-axis: Realized carry component only (not total return)

Add:

45Â° reference line

Interpretation:

Slope â‰ˆ 1 â†’ well-calibrated carry

Slope < 1 â†’ decay / slippage

Slope > 1 â†’ conservative model

This directly supports your:

â€œcarry explains â‰¥ 40% of returnâ€ criterion

5ï¸âƒ£ One plot that kills most objections (if you want to be surgical)
Rank IC over time

Compute Spearman rank correlation between expected carry and realized return per rebalance

Plot distribution (boxplot or histogram)

Why itâ€™s lethal:

Scale-free

No portfolio construction

No distributional assumptions

Time-local (no look-ahead accusations)

If median IC > 0 and stable â†’ alpha exists.

